{{Shrine | name = Todoroki Shrine | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image = [[File:Todoroki-shrine.jpg|250px]] | location = Miyano-kita 41, Aratano-chō, [[Anan]], [[Tokushima Prefecture]] | coordinates = {{Coord|33|50|51.2|N|134|34|42.5|E|type:landmark_region:JP-36|display=inline,title}} | deity = {{Ublist|[[Shinatsuhiko|級長津比古命]]|級長津比女}} | Shrine rank = | Foundation = [[814]] (Kōnin 1) | Main hall = | alternate_name = | Annual festival = | Rituals = | Map = {{location map|Japan Tokushima Prefecture|label=Todoroki Shrine|mark=Shinto torii icon vermillion.svg|marksize=20|float=center|border=none|width=200|caption=|relief=1}} }} '''Todoroki Shrine''' (轟神社, Todoroki Jinja) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} located in [[Aratano-chō]], [[Anan]], [[Tokushima Prefecture]].
== History == The shrine is believed to have been founded in [[814]] (Kōnin 1) by enshrining a divided spirit from {{ill|Tatsuta Shrine|ja|龍田神社|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Yamato Province|ja|Yamato Province|12=draft|12=draft}}. The enshrined deity, referred to as the Tatsuta Wind God, has long been venerated by farmers and maritime workers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.city.anan.tokushima.jp/docs/2010120800440/|title=Todoroki Shrine|publisher=Anan City|accessdate=2021-04-23}}</ref>
<gallery widths=200 heights=140> Todoroki-shrine front.jpg|Pathway from the shrine precincts </gallery>
== Deities == * [[Shinatsuhiko|級長津比古命]] * 級長津比女
== Aratano's Camphor Tree Grove == The shrine grounds feature a grove of camphor trees estimated to be over 700 years old. This grove is designated as a Natural Monument of Tokushima Prefecture. According to legend, two white snakes inhabit the roots of the largest tree. Occasionally appearing as messengers of Todoroki Myōjin, those who witness the snakes are said to receive good fortune.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.anan-kankou.jp/docs/2016120800022/|title=Todoroki Shrine|publisher=Anan City Tourism Association|accessdate=2021-04-23|url-status=dead|url-status-date=2024-09-19}}</ref>
<gallery> Todoroki-shrine 3.jpg Aratano-kusu-no-gunsei 4.jpg Aratano-kusu-no-gunsei 3.jpg Aratano-kusu-no-gunsei.jpg Todoroki-shrine 4.jpg Aratano-kusu-no-gunsei 2.jpg </gallery>
== Access == * Approximately 30 minutes on foot from [[Shikoku Railway Company|JR]] [[Mugi Line]]'s {{ill|Aratano Station|ja|新野駅 (徳島県)|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== References == <references />
== External Links == * [https://www.city.anan.tokushima.jp/docs/2010120800440/ Todoroki Shrine] - Anan City
